Students will be able to:
1. acquire updated and comprehensive knowledge of biomedical sciences through attending lectures, seminars and discussions with peers and teachers;
2. acquire an in-depth understanding of contemporary topical issues of biomedical sciences;
3. understand the applications and limitations of biomedical knowledge in various therapeutic designs;
4. develop self-learning abilities and critical thinking through reading scientific publications and expressing views on current scientific issues;
5. develop writing skills for scientific presentations and publications.

